# ALTERNATIVE NAME 2: Statement 2 - In general, the House of Lords is an important part of the British political system. It is a necessary check on the power of the House of Commons and its members are often more experienced and knowledgeable than their counterparts in the Commons. However, the current system of appointment is outdated and needs to be reformed. A small number of members of the House of Lords should be elected. This would ensure that the House of Lords is not completely out of touch with the views of the British people and that it is not seen as an elitist institution.
