# ALTERNATIVE NAME 4: Statement 4 - In general, the House of Lords should be elected. The current system of hereditary peers is outdated and should be abolished. However, there should be a certain number of seats in the House of Lords that are appointed by the Prime Minister. This would ensure that the House of Lords can remain independent from the House of Commons and would be able to provide an effective check and balance on the government.
